						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the central shrine in Svarṇapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I year 28: 1012-13 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription registers the gift of money for maintaining <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> daily to the deity probably of Pāradāyakuḍi, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Tirunaṟaiyūr-nāḍu in •••• khāmaṇi-vaḷanāḍu. The names of the donors and other details of the gift are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
